name: Morning Rosebud Dew
description: From the garden in the morning, when the dew has yet to leave, drops reflect the sunlight, dazzling as can be. I go to grab my camera, to capture fleeting beauty, mix it up together, and share with the community. Just a little poem for my Genesis piece here on Hic Et Nunc. This piece is a little different from my "usual style" as I've been exploring a light touch using digital tools I have recently found.
